Small Town Kid, Martin Flores will be coming home with a medal from the Great Southwest Classic. Marty wore yellow and red as he represented the State of New Mexico. States in attendance were Texas, Colorado, New Mexico, Utah, Arizona, Florida, and Oklahoma to name a few.
Martin placed 7th in the 1600 m. Run and made podium (6th) in the 3200 M. Run.
Way to represent for your home town and the State of New Mexico.
Congratulations! We are Proud of You and your hard work. #SuccessIsn'tGiven.It'sEarned.

post_text:
*** Bobcats, Lady Cats Class AA District Champions!!! ***

The Class AA District 4 Championship was held on Friday April 27th in Hagerman. Both Bobcat squads ended the night with a District Championship. On the men's side, the Bobcats finished with a total of 176.5 points while Jal came in 2nd with 148.5 points. This makes the Bobcats, Back to Back to Back District Champions. Martin Flores tied for High Point Athlete of the meet scoring 25.5 points. The Hagerman Lady Bobcats outscored Gateway 155 to152 for the win. Congratulations to all athletes who competed and qualified for State.

Special thanks to all those who went out and supported, donated to the hospitality room and donated snacks for our athletes.
A Big Thanks to the staff, parents, and community members who donated their time to help make this meet a successful event. You are Greatly Appreciated!!!

post_text:
Lady Cats Win Harvey Wilson Invite, Bobcats Place 2nd.

This past Friday, Hagerman hosted the 2018 Harvey Wilson/Alfalfa Capital Relays. Teams in attendance were Dexter, Eunice, Gateway, Hagerman, Jal, Lake Arthur, Loving, Mescalero, NMMI, and RHS Jv.

On the Men's side, the 2A Hagerman Bobcats placed 2nd, scoring a total of 83 points behind 3A Eunice with 98 points. The Bobcats finished the night with 8 qualified events.
On the women's side, the Hagerman Lady Bobcats took 1st, outscoring the Lady Eunice Cardinals by a score of 115 to 93. The Lady Cats 5 individual events and 2 relays qualified for the night.

Congratulations to All Track Athletes.

Special Thanks to all parents, school staff, and community members who helped make this meet a success. We truly appreciate your help and support.

Great to be a Bobcat!

On the Men's side, the 2A Hagerman Bobcats placed 2nd, scoring a total of 83 points behind 3A Eunice with 98 points. The Bobcats finished the night with 8 qualified events.
On the women's side, the Hagerman Lady Bobcats took 1st, outscoring the Lady Eunice Cardinals by a score of 115 to 93. The Lady Cats 5 individual events and 2 relays qualified for the night.

Congratulations to All Track Athletes.

Special Thanks to all parents, school staff, and community members who helped make this meet a success. We truly appreciate your help and support.

Great to be a Bobcat!

June 3, 2017 at 11:30 AM ·

Hagerman High School’s Martin Flores will represent New Mexico in the 2017 Great Southwest Classic.

Three athletes from Hagerman, New Mexico have been invited to the 42nd Annual Great Southwest Classic in Albuquerque, New Mexico; Senior, Sebastian Garcia, Senior, Isaac Morales, & Sophomore, Martin Flores.

Of the three athletes, Martin Flores has accepted the invitation to the meet and will get to showcase his talents in the Men’s 3200 M. Run & 1600 M. Run. This afternoon Martin will be wearing yellow and red as he will represent the State of New Mexico. Martin will compete against athletes from Arizona, Colorado, Florida, Illinois, Kansas, Louisiana Missouri, Nevada, New Mexico, Oklahoma, Texas, and Utah.

Good Luck Marty! You represent Hagerman very well and today, we know you will not just be a great representative for Hagerman, but for the State of New Mexico as well. Go get um Bobcat! Hagerman will be rooting for you!

post_text:
-Bobcats Take First at 2017 Alfalfa Capital Relays - (Hagerman, New Mexico)
Hagerman High School hosted the 2017 Alfalfa Capital Relays this week where 11 teams were in attendance from class 1A-3A. The 2A Hagerman Lady Bobcats placed 3rd (60 Points) behind 3A Loving (67 Points) & 3A Eunice (117 Points). The Lady Cats qualified for the State Championships in all 4 of their relays as well as 1 open event.
The Hagerman Bobcats (2A) demolished the competition scoring 153 points for the night. 3A Dexter placed 2nd (82 Points) followed by 3A Capitan with 65 points. The Bobcats qualified 11 events for the night.
Congratulations to all of the Hagerman Bobcats who competed in the meet. Keep working Hard! You're making Hagerman Proud!
• State Qualifying Pictures to come.

post_text:
*** 2 NEW SCHOOL RECORDS ***

In 1998 two school records were broken in the Men’s & Women’s 3200 M Run. Mayra Trevizo held the 3200 M. record with a time of 13:22.15, while D.Lozoya held the Men’s 3200 M. record with a time of 10:44.30. These records stood for 18 untouched years.

In April 2016, 8th Grader, Cerria Lucero broke Mayra’s 1998, 3200 M. Record by ½ a second with a time of 13:21.65.

On March 18th, 2016, Freshmen, Martin Flores broke D. Lozoya’s 18 year old record by 7 seconds with a time of 10:37.24. A month later, on April 15th Martin broke his own record with a time of 10:37.04. A week later on April 22nd, he once again broke that record with a time of 10:36.74. Martin was not finished there. A few weeks later Martin broke his own record once again, but this time at the State Track Meet with a time of 10:29.60, beating his previous record by 8 seconds and the 1998 record by 15 seconds.
A Big Congratulations to these young athletes & Good Luck in the years to come. Bobcat Pride!!
